The highly anticipated clash saw both teams unleash a captivating display of attacking football, resulting in a thrilling spectacle for spectators. Real Madrid's Karim Benzema and Manchester City's Riyad Mahrez emerged as the key players, each scoring a brace. Despite City's dominant performance for much of the game, Real Madrid showcased their resilience, battling back from a two-goal deficit to force extra time. The penalty shootout proved to be a tense affair, with Real Madrid ultimately triumphing 3-1 and securing a place in the semi-finals of the tournament.

summary: "Under the Bridge," a Hulu true crime drama, has garnered attention for its portrayal of the cruel and enigmatic nature of teenagehood. The series, based on a real-life murder, explores the circumstances surrounding two young women who were killed in different time periods. Lily Gladstone and Riley Keough's performances are praised for their emotional depth, while the series' handling of the familiar true-crime genre is noted for its nuanced approach, avoiding sensationalism in favor of a thoughtful examination of the factors that contribute to tragedy. While some critics find the show to be timid in its storytelling, others commend its ability to transcend the limitations of the "dead-girl show" formula and offer a poignant exploration of human relationships and the consequences of violence.

name: Mike Johnson
summary: Embattled Texas House Speaker Mike Johnson faces backlash over foreign aid decisions, with some Republicans seeking to remove him. Despite threats to his position, Johnson has met with former President Trump, who expressed support. Democrats are reportedly open to saving Johnson from a motion to vacate, while Johnson himself has vowed not to resign. Johnson's proposal to provide aid to Israel has drawn criticism, with one Republican lawmaker supporting a move to remove him as Speaker. Amidst these challenges, Johnson is reportedly negotiating with the White House to advance Ukraine aid, while Democrats are said to be fueling GOP discontent over his foreign aid policies.

name: Mayorkas
summary: The House of Representatives recently sent articles of impeachment against Secretary of Homeland Security Alejandro Mayorkas to the Senate, leading to a trial. The impeachment trial was considered historic, as it is rare for a cabinet member to face such charges.

name: Steve Harvey
summary: Steve Harvey has been making headlines lately, with various stories circulating about him and his family. His wife, Marjorie, has been criticized for her activism, leading to a discussion on his show about the appropriate time for activism. In a separate incident, a contestant on "Family Feud" walked off the stage, leaving Harvey stunned. Harvey has also denied rumors of an affair that led to the breakup of his previous marriage. Meanwhile, Ed Lover has confirmed allegations that Harvey betrayed his late friend Bernie Mac. Harvey's daughter has recently made her relationship with Michael B. Jordan Instagram official. Despite rumors, Harvey is alive and well, and he continues to host his popular morning show. Additionally, his daughter-in-law has shaved her head, sparking the attention of the internet.

name: Chris Paul
summary: Despite speculation, Chris Paul has announced his intention to continue playing for the Warriors in the upcoming NBA season. However, the team's plans for the future remain uncertain, with reports indicating that they have no plans to tank but face challenges in making decisions regarding Klay Thompson and Paul's status. The high salary and potential roster fit of Paul make his long-term future with the team questionable. Despite the uncertainty, Paul has committed to another season, and the Warriors are aiming for success in the playoffs. Paul has also made headlines for his partnership with a Black-woman-owned fintech company to promote financial literacy in Oakland.

summary: Grammy Award-winning R&B singer Ashanti and rapper Nelly are getting married and having a baby together.
